The paper discusses the behavior of Spiking Neural Networks (SNN) under adversarial attacks, which falls under the category of neural networks and machine learning. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses the CIFAR-10 dataset and performs image classification, which falls under the computer vision sub-category (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the accuracy degradation of SNN compared to conventional Artificial Neural Networks (ANN), which falls under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the training mechanism of SNN and its impact on adversarial robustness, which falls under the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and systems and control (cs.SY).
